HJR284 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2
3 COMMENDING MOLLY MEADOWS ON THE OCCASION OF HER RETIREMENT.
4
5 WHEREAS, it is with profound appreciation and highest
6 esteem that Molly Meadows is honored for her exceptional
7 dedication, commitment, and professionalism throughout her
8 tenure serving Houston County, Alabama, for nearly four
9 decades; and
10 WHEREAS, Molly Meadows was first appointed by Albert
11 McDonald, Secretary of Agriculture under the Governor Guy
12 Hunt Administration, in 1987; she served through 10 cycles
13 for presidential, gubernatorial, and local elections with
14 distinction as Chairman of the Board of Registrars in
15 Houston County, contributing significantly to maintaining
16 the integrity of the voter registration process and
17 encouragement of every person's right to vote; and
18 WHEREAS, she has exemplified the highest standards of
19 public service, good character, and servant leadership,
20 making the voter registration process available and
21 accessible for all residents of Houston County; and
22 WHEREAS, Molly was married for 58 years to Robert
23 Brook "Bo" Meadows before he passed in 2018; Mr. Meadows
24 worked in the business license division of the Houston
25 County Judge of Probate's Office; both Molly and Bo were
26 involved in civic and community service; Molly has a son,
27 Brook Meadows; daughters, Misty Sheffield and Holly
28 Gagliano; 10 grandchildren; and seven great-grandchildren;
Page 1

Gagliano; 10 grandchildren; and seven great-grandchildren;
HJR284 Enrolled
29 and
30 WHEREAS, it is the desire of the Legislature to
31 recognize and honor Molly Meadows for her invaluable
32 contributions, undeniable passion for her work, and loyal
33 service to Houston County and the State of Alabama upon the
34 occasion of her retirement effective March 31, 2026; now
35 therefore,
36 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, BOTH
37 HOUSES THEREOF CONCURRING, That Molly Meadows is hereby
38 commended on the occasion of her retirement as Chairman of
39 the Board of Registrars in Houston County, and this
40 resolution is offered to her in highest tribute and with
41 deepest appreciation along with best wishes as she embarks
42 upon her well-deserved retirement.
